This paper is about a neural machine translation model that takes into account both the source and target document contexts using memory networks. The model is trained end-to-end and uses a structured prediction approach with interdependencies among the observed and hidden variables. Given the focus on natural language processing and machine learning, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of memory networks and neural translation models also suggests possible categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions experimental results and analysis on translating documents, which could also indicate a possible category such as cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) if the documents include visual information.
